<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,440,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Storch, 1967" authorityName="Storch" authorityYear="1967" box="[325,728,439,464]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="magnipectinis">
<emphasis box="[325,553,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Syllis magnipectinis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Storch" box="[571,720,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="Storch, V. (1967) Neue Polychaeten aus der Sandfauna des Roten Meeres. Zoologische Anzeiger, 178 (1 / 2), 101 - 110." type="journal article" year="1967">
Storch, 
<number box="[662,720,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1967.0">1967</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
belongs to a small group of species characterized by having falcigers with a considerably large subdistal tooth and large subdistal spines: 
<taxonomicName authority="Nunez" authorityName="Nunez" authorityYear="1991" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cruzi">
<emphasis box="[1049,1176,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Syllis cruzi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="Nunez, J. &amp; San Martin, G. (1991) Two new species of Syllidae (Polychaeta) from Tenerife (Canary Islands, Spain). Bulletin of Marine Science, 48 (2), 236 - 241." type="journal article" year="1991">
Núñez &amp; San Martín, 
<number box="[151,209,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Westheide, 1974" authorityName="Westheide" authorityYear="1974" box="[222,612,511,536]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="glarearia">
<emphasis box="[222,396,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Syllis glarearia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Westheide" box="[412,605,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="Westheide, W. (1974) Interstitielle Fauna von Galapagos XI. Pisionidae, Hesionidae, Pilargidae, Syllidae (Polychaeta). Mikrofauna des Meeresbodens, 44, 1 - 146." type="journal article" year="1974">
Westheide, 
<number box="[545,605,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1974.0">1974</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Nogueira &amp; Yunda-Guarin, 2008" authorityName="Nogueira &amp; Yunda-Guarin" authorityYear="2008" box="[625,1154,511,536]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="guidae">
<emphasis box="[625,770,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Syllis guidae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira" box="[779,1154,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="Nogueira, J. M. &amp; Yunda-Guarin, G. (2008) A new species of Syllis (Polychaeta: Syllidae: Syllinae) from off Fortaleza, northeastern Brazil. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 88 (7), 1391 - 1399." type="journal article" year="2008">
Nogueira &amp; Yunda-Guarín, 
<number box="[1095,1154,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1166,1301,512,536]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="jorgei">
<emphasis box="[1166,1301,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Syllis jorgei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="San" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="San Martin, G. &amp; Lopez, E. (2000) Three new species of Syllis (Syllidae: Polychaeta) from Iberian coasts. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 41, 425 - 433." type="journal article" year="2000">
San Martín &amp; López, 
<number box="[274,333,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartmann-Schroder, 1960" authorityName="Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1960" box="[349,805,548,572]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis box="[349,478,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Syllis lutea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann-Schroder" box="[498,797,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="Hartmann-Schroder, G. (1960) Polychaeten aus dem Roten Meer. Kieter Meeresforschungen, 16, 69 - 125." type="journal article" year="1960">
Hartmann-Schröder, 
<number box="[740,797,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1960.0">1960</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[870,1002,548,572]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ortizi">
<emphasis box="[870,1002,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Syllis ortizi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="San" box="[1014,1223,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="San Martin, G. (1992) Syllis Savigny in Lamarck, 1818 (Polychaeta: Syllidae: Syllinae) from Cuba, the Gulf of Mexico, Florida and North Carolina, with a revision of several species described by Verrill. Bulletin of Marine Science, 51, 167 - 196." type="journal article" year="1992">
San Martín, 
<number box="[1164,1223,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
. Nonetheless, this species is characterized by having midbody and posterior enlarged falcigers with very thick blades and a prominent subtriangular subdistal tooth, more than five times larger than the distal one. 
<taxonomicName box="[1053,1281,620,644]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="magnipectinis">
<emphasis box="[1053,1281,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Syllis magnipectinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[275,368,656,680]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ortizi">
<emphasis box="[275,368,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">S. ortizi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, some specimens from the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[900,985,655,679]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Mexico</collectingCountry>
have been confused, since they were originally assigned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Uebelacker" box="[405,614,692,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="Uebelacker, J. M. (1984) Family Syllidae Grube, 1850. In Taxonomic guide to the polychaetes of the northern Gulf of Mexico, vol. IV. Uebelacker, J. M. &amp; Johnson, P. G. (Eds.) Barry A. Vittor and Associates, Mobile, 1 - 151." type="book chapter" year="1984">
Uebelacker (
<number box="[547,605,692,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1984.0">1984</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
to a single species named 
<taxonomicName box="[913,974,692,716]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[913,974,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Syllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. A but later recognized by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="San Martin, G. (1992) Syllis Savigny in Lamarck, 1818 (Polychaeta: Syllidae: Syllinae) from Cuba, the Gulf of Mexico, Florida and North Carolina, with a revision of several species described by Verrill. Bulletin of Marine Science, 51, 167 - 196." type="journal article">
San Martín (
<number box="[159,217,727,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1992.0">1992</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Storch" box="[287,445,727,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="Storch, V. (1995) Redescription of Typosyllis magnipectinis (Storch, 1967) from the South China Sea. Senckenbergiana maritima, 25 (4 / 6), 107 - 113." type="journal article" year="1995">
Storch (
<number box="[379,437,727,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as the two species mentioned above. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[1012,1103,728,752]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ortizi">
<emphasis box="[1012,1103,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">S. ortizi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has falcigers with a smaller subdistal tooth, and distal spines extending beyond the distal tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
Most specimens from Acapulco differ slightly from those described by 
<bibRefCitation box="[1025,1254,799,824]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="Licher, F., Ding, Z., Fiege, D. &amp; Sun, R. (1995) Redescription of Typosyllis magnipectinis (Storch, 1967) from the South China Sea. Senckenbergiana maritima, 25 (4 / 6), 107 - 113." type="journal article">
Licher 
<emphasis box="[1107,1166,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1184,1245,799,823]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, such variations could be size-related, as small specimens have wider and shorter palps, robust falcigers lacking small basal spines, and normal falcigers with shorter blades (a character that is also size-dependent in other species such as 
<taxonomicName box="[181,326,908,932]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="guidae">
<emphasis box="[181,326,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Syllis guidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and larger distal spinulation. Large specimens have larger and thinner palps, the blades of normal falcigers are larger and, in most cases, the spinulation becomes uniform, thus being more similar to the original description. The other examined characters agree well with the original diagnosis. Originally described from the Red Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Storch" box="[259,405,1015,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" refString="Storch, V. (1967) Neue Polychaeten aus der Sandfauna des Roten Meeres. Zoologische Anzeiger, 178 (1 / 2), 101 - 110." type="journal article" year="1967">
Storch, 
<number box="[348,405,1015,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1967.0">1967</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and later recorded in the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[793,878,1015,1039]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and in the South 
<collectingCountry box="[1079,1146,1015,1039]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">China</collectingCountry>
Sea, the present record is the first for the eastern Pacific. Therefore, the species may be considered as circumtropical, being now known from the tropical zones of the three major oceans of the world.
</paragraph>
